**$x$-intercept:** Set $y = 0$.
\[
 2x - 5(0) = 10 \implies x = 5
\]
The $x$-intercept is $(5, 0)$.

**$y$-intercept:** Set $x = 0$.
\[
 2(0) - 5y = 10 \implies -5y = 10 \implies y = -2
\]
The $y$-intercept is $(0, -2)$.

**Check point:** Let $x = -5$.
\[
 2(-5) - 5y = 10 \implies -10 - 5y = 10 \implies y = -4
\]
The point $(-5, -4)$ should lie on the line.

